        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>SECTION 7.  EXTENSION OF LIBERATIVE PRESCRIPTION
Art. 3505.  Acts extending liberative prescription
After liberative prescription has commenced to run but before it accrues, an obligor may by juridical act extend the prescriptive period.  An obligor may grant successive extensions.  The duration of each extension may not exceed one year.</p>
        </content>
